{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566469","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566469"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:41:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:41:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18832"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18832","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18832"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.19,0.24,0.41,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11565"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79618"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11565","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11565"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18832"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64922"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11290"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27218"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27229"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27237"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79618"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student asks for guidance about what constitutes medical professionalism. The student has observed different behaviours and attitudes among healthcare workers and wants to understand the core principles.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes medical professionalism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Demonstrating excellence in clinical skills while maintaining emotional boundaries","Upholding ethical standards while preserving clinical autonomy","Prioritising evidence-based practice while respecting cultural differences","Maintaining clinical competence while prioritising patient welfare above self-interest","Balancing patient advocacy with resource stewardship"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct definition of medical professionalism involves \u003Cstrong\u003Emaintaining clinical competence while prioritising patient welfare above self-interest\u003C/strong\u003E. This encompasses multiple elements including ethical practice, accountability, respect for patients and colleagues, cultural sensitivity, and commitment to excellence in clinical care.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDemonstrating excellence in clinical skills while maintaining emotional boundaries\u003C/strong\u003E - While clinical excellence and boundaries are important, this definition omits the crucial element of putting patient interests first\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUpholding ethical standards while preserving clinical autonomy\u003C/strong\u003E - This overemphasises practitioner autonomy rather than patient-centred care\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrioritising evidence-based practice while respecting cultural differences\u003C/strong\u003E - Though these are components of professionalism, this definition is too narrow and misses key aspects like accountability and patient welfare\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBalancing patient advocacy with resource stewardship\u003C/strong\u003E - While resource management is relevant, it should not be elevated to a defining characteristic of professionalism\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EMedical professionalism is fundamentally about maintaining high standards of competence and ethical behaviour while putting patients\u0027 interests first. This includes continuous professional development, effective communication, respect for patient autonomy, and working collaboratively with colleagues.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical professionalism encompasses competence, ethics, accountability, respect, and commitment to patient welfare above self-interest.","Professionalism requires maintaining appropriate boundaries while showing empathy and compassion.","Professional behaviour includes effective communication, collaboration, and continuous self-improvement."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Australian Medical Association. Medical Professionalism - 2010. Revised 2015. [online]. 2015. [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.ama.com.au/position-statement/medical-professionalism-2010-revised-2015","RACP. Consensus Statement: Medical Professionalism in a changing context: Beyond specialties; Beyond Borders. [online]. 2012. [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.racp.edu.au/docs/default-source/advocacy-library/consensus-statement---medical-professionalism.pdf?sfvrsn=22ac2c1a_2"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64922"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18832"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64922","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64922"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T11:12:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T11:13:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11565"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79618"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":fa